A Scottish study revealed that statins can reduce heart disease risk for men with short telomeres.
Telomere length measurement in middle-aged men could identify those at risk.
A gene variant predisposes women to heart disease, while gum disease increases pancreatic cancer risk.
Gum disease may also be linked to heart disease.
A heart peptide test can predict severe heart disease consequences.
Congenital heart disease prevalence is rising in adults and children.
Stress in childhood may lead to inflammation and heart disease later in life.
Air pollution increases cardiovascular disease risk for postmenopausal women.
Reducing pollution could lower disease rates.
